Title: Given/When/Then test convention

Scope: **tests** (`**/*.test.ts`, `**/*.spec.ts`)

Rule:
- Each test block must clearly separate three phases with comments:
  - `// Given` for setup
  - `// When` for exercising the system under test
  - `// Then` for assertions

Guidance:
- Prefer one assertion group under the `// Then` section.
- Keep setup minimal; use factories/helpers for noisy data.
- Name tests in behavior terms, not implementation details.

Examples:

Bad:
```ts
it('does X', () => {
  const a = 1; doSomething(a);
  expect(result).toBe(1);
});
```

Good:
```ts
it('does X', () => {
  // Given
  const a = 1;

  // When
  const result = doSomething(a);

  // Then
  expect(result).toBe(1);
});
```

